         <abstract>
            <p>The properties of German as a special language of mechanical engineering are examined on the basis of a newly compiled corpus including samples from all important disciplines and discourse styles. The syntactic, semantic, and pragmatic aspects of passive voice are the chief research goal, necessary in order to evaluate the existing and to develop new courseware. Other linguistic and metalinguistic features of the sublanguage will be investigated and transferred into teaching theory and practice.</p>
         </abstract>
